{
  "text": "For the ImageNet task, we set N=3 and add more pooling operation before blocks. We use the best block structure learned from CIFAR-10 directly without any fine-tuning, and initialized with MSRA initialization same as above. The experimental results are shown in Table 4 . The model generated by our framework can get competitive result compared with other human designed models. The recently proposed methods such as Xception (Chollet 2016) and ResNext [CITATION_1] ) use special depth-wise convolution operation to reduce its total number of parameters and to improve performance, in our work, we do not use this new convolution operation, so it can't be compared fairly, and we will consider this in our future work to further improve the performance.",
